name: Ika Hapsari
review: (Translated by Google) Meatball stall located in front of Superindo Banyumanik. The price of the meatball is 18 thousand. The complete portion comes with large meatballs, small meatballs, yellow noodles, vermicelli, mustard greens, and offal. The portions are quite large and filling, worth the price. name: inggar putri
review: (Translated by Google) Do you know the boxed meatballs when I bought them here in high school in 2008. The prices are cheap with large portions. The noodles are not stingy at all. In a bowl, you get 1 box of meatballs (large meatballs cut into squares), 1 quail egg meatball, 2 muscle meatballs, 1 meatball tofu. But here I'm changing meatballs because I don't really like tofu and I use white corn noodles instead of so'un. That's the type of broth, not the clear, fresh one, because the boxed meatballs have a mixture like that, which if you get hot sauce, it turns into oil, I don't know what it's called. Recommend hot oranges to drink. First, because the gravy is oily so the oranges are fresher, secondly because they haven't used ice crystals so it's better if you cough easily, and thirdly because the iced tea isn't that good. A portion of meatballs + iced tea = just 18k I like the small meatballs compared to the box meatballs and the quail egg meatballs. It's more meaty and chewy, for some reason. (Original) Kenal bakso kotak ya pas beli disini jaman smp tahun 2008. Harganya murah dengan porsi yang banyak. Mienya pun nggak pelit sama sekali. Semangkuk dapat 1 bakso kotak (bakso besar dipotong2 kotak), 1 bakso telur puyuh, 2 bakso urat, 1 tahu bakso. Tapi disini aku ganti bakso karena emang nggak begitu doyan tahu yaa dan pake mie putih jagung bukan so'un. Tipe kuah kaldu gitu yaa, bukan yang bening segar karena bakso kotaknya itu ada campuran gitu yang kalo kena kuah panas jadi minyak gitu, apa namanya nggak tahu. Rekomen jeruk panas untuk minumnya. Pertama karena kuah berminyak jadi kalo jeruk lebih segar, kedua karena belum pake es kristal jadi mending anget aja kalo kalian gampang batuk, dan ketiga karena es teh nya ngga terlalu enak sih. Seporsi bakso + es teh = 18k aja Aku suka bakso kecil2nya dibanding bakso kotak sama bakso telur puyuhnya. Lebih kerasa dagingnya dan kenyal sih, entah kenapa. Parking: Limited parking

name: Yasser Wahyuddin
review: Yes this is the best bakso you could find around Banyumanik and Tembalang area in Semarang. The place is not too cozy but it hides plentyful authenticity of Bakso. To reach this place easily you need Google maps direction.

name: Muhammad Afif
review: Ey ey, The best bakso (Indonesian Meatballs) in upper semarang city. Affordable price with serious taste. The solid round of beef and starch mixture bring tremendous pleasure. Chewiness and great aroma will bring you here again and again. You can order bakso-es in a great bakso, also tendon-dissolved meatballs or "Bakso Urat" and adding floating quasi-solid tallow in your bowl. Finally, iced tea and orange juice will quench your thirst . Very hungry? add lontong or double your noodle. Feel something to crunch? there are also different type of kerupuk here. name: Arief Said
review: (Translated by Google) The meatballs are delicious and chewy, the sauce is still clear and light, even though it's mixed with offal in the pot. Maybe it will be different if it comes at night, the gravy can be thicker and thicker. You can choose meatballs plus offal or plain. There are no drops / balungan. The white noodles use vermicelli, while the yellow ones use egg noodles. There's tofu pong as an addition and free pickled cucumber if it's still available... The place is a roadside tent which if it's full, it can get crowded and even queue up, even though there are two additional tables outside the tent... (Original) Baksonya enak dan kenyal, kuahnya tetep bening dan ringan, meski dicampur jeroan di dandangnya. Mungkin akan berbeda jika datangnya malam, kuah bisa lebih kental dan eneg. Bisa pilih bakso plus jeroan atau polos. Tidak ada tetelan /balungan. Mienya yang putih pake soun, sedang yang kuning mie telor. Ada tahu pong sebagai tambahan dan free acar timun jika masih ada... Tempatnya tenda pinggir jalan yang jika penuh, bisa sesak bahkan ngantri, meski ada dua meja tambahan di luar tenda...

name: Regina FY
review: (Translated by Google) Try this Baso at night, the location is next to the transmart near the intersection. Ask the father, it is open from 12.30 to 21.00, the price of the Baso is IDR 19,000 per serving. How does it feel? Yummy The bass is bouncy, supple, solid, not soft when you bite it. The gravy is hot too. The sambal is spicy Then earlier, we were making dinner so we beat the rice too. The rice is delicious too, fluffier, clean white. There are ready to swallow/offal too, just because it was finished, it's not there anymore. You can choose vermicelli or yellow noodles too. On the table there is a choice of fried tofu as well as snacks to eat with the baso. Overall it's delicious, if you go to Semarang again, this will be on the list of Must-Try Foods (Original) Nyobain Baso ini pas kulineran malem, lokasi di samping transmart deket simpang lima itu. Nanya si bapak nya buka dari jam 12.30 sampai jam 21.00, Harga Baso nya IDR 19,000 per porsi. Rasa nya gimana ? Enakkk Baso nya mantul, kenyel, padet, gak gembos gt digigit. Kuah nya juga panas. Sambel nya pedessss Trus tadi kita-kita kan buat makan malem jadi hajar nasi juga. Nasi nya enak juga, pulen, putih bersih. Ada sedia tetelan/jeroan juga, cuma krn tadi penghabisan, uda gak ada. Bisa pilih bihun atau mie kuning juga. Di meja ada pilihan tahu goreng juga buat cemal cemil makan sama si baso. Overall enak, klo ke Semarang lagi, ini bakal masuk list Makanan Wajib Coba
